The rustic table is filled with knife marks, faded charcoal etchings, and the stains of spilt food.

A notice on the board reads 'Any vagabonds and miscreants doing damage to this shop be hereby warned, by Order of Laird MacFeargus, all vandalism to shops be they sellers of goods enchanted and mystical, or also of goods mundane, will be put in stocks and on a second offence will lose a hand. The selling of magical goods is approved by this Order and by the Laird himself.
-Captain Tomlin, MacFeargus Militia'
The chains on these floor-bound shackles are chipped and marked as if someone had been pounding on them with a rock. Whoever it was, it doesn't appear that their efforts met with any success.

LORE SUCCESS!!! This is Kingsbay, well known to be the busiest port on the isle of Gwynneth, supposedly sits on the original landing site of the forebears of Ffolk, led by the fabled Gwynneth Randol, "the First Mother". More likely however the settlers made landfall upon the southern shores, due to the high cliffs and treacherous shoals which mark the Kingsbay and may still prove deadly to the more careless of the many merchant ships which seek to make port here. The sound of the sea, clatter and rumble of winches at the docks, and the yells of sailors and tradesmen flood your ears...

LORE SUCCESS!!! Clan MacFeargus are an old clan that claim much of the territory of Cantrev Kingsbay. Their wealth is founded on the shipping trade of Kingsbay, the only port on Gwynneth that sustains strong links with Mintarn and the distant Sword Coast cities. The old Laird Aaron MacFeargus is known as a fair and honest broker, but in recent years his elderly fist has come down hard upon common criminals and smugglers that seem to multiply day by day in the mercantile hub of this bustling sea port...

LORE SUCCESS!!! The cliff-side docks of Kingsbay stretch out beneath you, a mercantile hive crawling with dockers, sailors, and other professionals of an even less salubrious kind. Kingsbay is well known as Gwynneth's only major link with Myntarn and the far-off cities of the Sword Coast. It also carries on a busy trade with the capital of the High Queen's realm - Callidyr, on neighbouring Alaron. The town is also known to welcome Amnian traders, who stop at Kingsbay to collect huge cut pine trees felled from the great forests of Gwynneth, transporting them to the shipyards of Orlumbor and Mintarn. Further south along the coast, the town of Horstall has long attempted to gain a portion of the eastern trade, but the extent of the great docks before you and stretching along the cliffs is testament to the town of Kingsbay's dominant position, squatting as it does on the edge of Gwynneth and the edge of the world. On very clear days, it is sometimes possible to see the tips of the Andover Heights, the great mountain range on western Snowdown, just peaking over the eastern horizon above the vast stretch of sea before you...
